or a formal work, neither an autobiographical narrative nor a work of the imagination, neither prose nor poetry, but all this at the same time. . . . A perpetual work in progress.”  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aAnthropologistszFrancevBiography. 0aPoets, FrenchvBiography. 0aSurrealism (Literature)zFrance. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Literary.2bisacsh1 aSieburth, Richard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2024z978311074979340uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/9780300277517?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300277517423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300277517/original  a978-3-11-074979-3  Yale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2024b2024  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles